Introduction:

This is a small(ish) maze game with 8 levels, the ability to save and some very annoying speech!!


It is the most completed game I ever wrote. It was written around 2-3 years ago (took a year or
so to get this far), originally programmed in EasyAMOS, but half way through I got hold of Blitz
Basic so I converted to that. It was going to go in the Reader Games section of Amiga
Format, but unfortunatly the Mag closed the month I submitted it. So here it is, finally in the
public domain - it's not a terribly exciting game, but enjoy it anyway :-)


This game was about the first game I got to a playable state. It was planned to have 100 levels in
addition to 5 boss races (race a boss around a maze), multiplayer support etc. Most of this was
never put in, so you only get 8 mazes here (and no races). It is certainly not what I would call
completed, but contray to what I wrote in the readme of the previous TCOT upload, I DO intend to
improve the game. 

PLEASE e-mail me if you have played the game, even if you didn't like it I'd still like to hear from
you!


